value.0: Atropa Belladonna is a well known and common growing plant, usually maintained in a shrub. The berries of the plant are often used by noble women to dilate the pupils of their eyes, though in large amounts the plant may also be used as a poison.

Belladonna is a common plant that seems to have an adverse effect on were-creatures. The plant is used like a potion and will temporarily protect the user from shapechanger attacks for a duration of one turn.

Found in dry gullies in semi-arid temperate zones, this herb thickens blood very quickly upon direct contact and can be applied to open wounds to slow or stop bleeding. In the proper hands, it can be used to help save a life.
Often found in dry gullies in semi-arid temperate zones, this herb thickens blood very quickly upon direct contact, and so can be applied to open wounds to slow or stop bleeding.

Garlic is a commonly used herb for cooking and is closely related to onions, challots, leeks, and chives. There are many uses for garlic, but it is usually consumed by the peasantry as a palliative for the heat of the sun.
Garlic is well known as a herb for flavoring foods and treating heat stroke among the preasantry. It is also used to repulse vampires.
Tall and proud, the silverbark birch is a somewhat rare occurance. The tree oozes a sap that can act as a minor antitoxin when used by the proper hands.
The sap of the silverbark tree is clear and slightly sticky. It acts as a minor antitoxin, granting anyone who consumes at least 1 ounce a +2 alchemical bonus on Fort saves towards poison for 1 hour.
